 scatter in RVs obtained with EXPRES from 4.72 m s$^{-1}$ to\n1.98 m s$^{-1}$. We present a pilot study using the CHARA Array and MIRC-X beam\ncombiner to directly image the starspots seen in the TESS photometry. With the\nlimited phase coverage, our spot detections are marginal with current data but\na future dedicated observing campaign should allow for imaging, as well as the\nstellar inclination and orientation with respect to its debris disk to be\ndefinitely determined. This work shows that stellar surface maps obtained with\nhigh cadence, time-series photometric and interferometric data can provide the\nconstraints needed to accurately reduce RV scatter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Oct 2021 16:24:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-22"}
