ds to the\ngrowing number of well-aligned planets at young ages, hinting that\nmisalignments may be generated over timescales of longer than tens of Myr. The\nnumber of measurements, however, is still small, and this population may not be\nrepresentative of the older planets that have been observed to date. We also\npresent the derivation of the relationship between $i_{\\mathrm{mut}}$,\n$\\lambda$, and $i$ for two planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Oct 2021 18:03:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Mar 2022 15:49:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-18"}
