oduce the current GW observations: a top-heavy stellar initial mass\nfunction and the presence of close binary stars for Pop III and EMP binary\nstars, and inefficient convective overshoot in the main-sequence phase of\nstellar evolution. Without any of the above, the number of PI mass gap events\nbecomes too low to reproduce current GW observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Oct 2021 01:23:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 11 Dec 2021 02:40:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 18 Feb 2022 10:17:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 2 Mar 2022 06:59:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-03"}
